menu "Web UI"

config WEBUI_MINING_UI
    bool "Serve the mining-mode web dashboard (SPA)"
    default y
    help
      Register the static mining dashboard SPA on the HTTP server. Assets are
      served as pre-gzipped blobs straight from flash (the browser decompresses),
      so the runtime heap cost is just the httpd response buffers.

      The /api/* routes are always registered regardless of this option, so a
      headless device still exposes stats, pool config, and OTA endpoints.

      Disable only on parts too heap-constrained to serve the dashboard without
      risking OOM (the no-PSRAM ESP32-S2 Mini). The C3 SuperMini and dual-core
      boards leave this on.

endmenu
